cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new method for video representation learning using 4D convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on improving the temporal evolution of spatio-temporal features in video data, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new 4D residual block, which is a novel contribution to the field of deep learning, and thus, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper conducts experiments on video recognition benchmarks, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed method also involves training and inference methods, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
